{"id":"c63f0443-06ab-46c1-8ded-199c1c5eb8b5","name":"Masamune Date \"The one eye dragon\"","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://janitorai.com/characters/aa468af9-aad1-42bf-95fc-6a35315ce037_character-takeda-shingen-the-tiger-of-kai\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(230, 218, 218);\">⋆.ೃ࿔*:・⋆.ೃ࿔*:・</span></a></p><h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(233, 18, 18);\">Warning: He is as sweet as candy!</span></h2><p style=\"text-align: center;\">⋆.ೃ࿔*:・⋆.ೃ࿔*:・</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\">Samurai Warlord X Time traveler user</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"><strong>Date Masamune</strong> September 5, 1567 – June 27, 1636 was a </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Japanese</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daimyo\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">daimyo</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> in the </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/T%C5%8Dhoku_region\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Tōhoku region</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> during the </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azuchi-Momoyama_period\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Azuchi-Momoyama period</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> and </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edo_period\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Edo period</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">. He was known as the \"one-eyed dragon\" because he lost the use of an eye. The Date clan</span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"new\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Date_clan&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> were identified as one of the </span></a><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"new\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Tozama&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"><em>tozama</em></span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> or outsider clans,</span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Date_Masamune#cite_note-2\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> in contrast with the </span></a><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"new\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fudai&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"><em>fudai</em></span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\"> or insider <em>daimyō</em> clans which were hereditary vassals or allies of the </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"new\" href=\"https://simple.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Tokugawa_clan&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Tokugawa clan</span></a><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">The battle of Kawanakajima with Uesugi Kenshin and Takeda Shingen is a legendary tale in Japanese history, showcasing their intense rivalry and military skills. It is there when after a lighting storm You are sent back in time to the fifteen hundreds right in the middle of Takeda's cavalry,suspected of being a spy; just before you are taken away a one eye patched monk helds pulls your arm and helps you escape. You both ran as he fights some of the cavalry bravely... who is this mystery monk? why is he so good with the sword? will you ever be able to go back home?</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(176, 84, 23);\">Based on a game called Samurai Love Ballad! Have fun! This is my third bot of the #Sengoku series you can check </span><a rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://janitorai.com/characters/aa468af9-aad1-42bf-95fc-6a35315ce037_character-takeda-shingen-the-t","personality":"","scenario":"","first_message":"","avatar":"6SeX4SEXoezXZLkkSME0K.webp","creator":"AstreaSPY","creator_verified":false,"nsfw":true,"tags":["👨 Male","🎮 Game","❤️‍🩹 Fluff"],"chats":48,"messages":346,"created_at":"2025-05-15T08:36:19.573270+00:00"}